properties.NAME: Sundarban
properties.DESCRIPTIO: A mangrove area in the delta formed by the confluence of the Ganges, Brahmaputra and Meghna Rivers in the Bay of Bengal.

properties.NAME: St. Martin's Island
properties.DESCRIPTIO: A  small island (area only 3 km2) in the northeastern part of the Bay of Bengal, about 9 km south of the tip of the Cox's Bazar-Teknaf peninsula, and forming the southernmost part of Bangladesh

properties.NAME: Ahasan Manjil
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Ahsan Manzil is the erstwhile official residential palace and seat of the Nawab of Dhaka

properties.NAME: Ratargul
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Ratargul Swamp Forest is a freshwater swamp forest located in Gowain River, Fatehpur Union, Gowainghat, Sylhet, Bangladesh.

properties.NAME: Lalbag Fort
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Lalbagh Fort is an incomplete 17th-century Mughal fort complex that stands before the Buriganga River in the southwestern part of Dhaka, Bangladesh.

properties.NAME: Sompur Bihar
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Somapura Mahavihara in Paharpur, Badalgachhi, Naogaon, Bangladesh is among the best known Buddhist viharas, monasteries, in the Indian Subcontinent and is one of the most important archaeological sites in the country.

properties.NAME: Sompur Bihar
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Somapura Mahavihara in Paharpur, Badalgachhi, Naogaon, Bangladesh is among the best known Buddhist viharas, monasteries, in the Indian Subcontinent and is one of the most important archaeological sites in the country.

properties.NAME: Jatiyo Sansad
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Jatiya Sangsad Bhaban or National Parliament House is the house of the Parliament of Bangladesh, located at Sher-e-Bangla Nagar in the Bangladeshi capital of Dhaka.

properties.NAME: Kua Kata
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Kuakata is a town in southern Bangladesh known for its panoramic sea beach. Kuakata beach is a sandy expanse 18 kilometres (11 mi) long and 3 kilometres (1.9 mi) wide.

properties.NAME: Dhakeshawari Mandir
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Dhakeshwari National Temple is a Hindu temple in Dhaka, Bangladesh.

properties.NAME: Sath Gambuj Masjid
properties.DESCRIPTIO: The Sixty Dome Mosque more commonly known as Shait Gambuj Mosque or Saith Gunbad Masjid, is a mosque in Bagerhat, Bangladesh.

properties.NAME: Boga Lake
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Bogakain Lake, also called Baga Lake or Boga Lake, is a lake located in Ruma Upazila in the hill district Bandarban, Bangladesh.It is a natural sweet and deep water lake. Its height from sea level is nearly 1,246 feet (380 m).

properties.NAME: Lawachara Forest
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Lawachara National Park is a major national park and nature reserve in Bangladesh. The park is located at Kamalganj Upazila, Moulvibazar District in the northeastern region of the country.

properties.NAME: Chimbuk Hill
properties.DESCRIPTIO: The Chimbuk hills Or Pahar of Bandarban, known as Darjeeling in Bengal. Chimbuk is the third largest mountain in Bangladesh.

properties.NAME: Golden Temple
properties.DESCRIPTIO: The Buddha Dhatu Jadi is known as the Bandarban Golden Temple, which is 4 Km away from the Bandorban town.

properties.NAME: Kanta Ji Temple
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Kantanagar Temple, commonly known as Kantaji Temple or Kantajew Temple at Kantanagar,is a late-medieval Hindu temple in Dinajpur, Bangladesh.

properties.NAME: Sapno puri
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Sapnapuri is a phony redirection park arranged in Aftabganj in Nawabganj upazila of Rangpur division of Bangladesh.

properties.NAME: Tajhat Jamidar
properties.DESCRIPTIO: Tajhat Palace is a historic palace of Bangladesh, located in Tajhat, Rangpur.
